e-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Context: </strong> <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Board members are experts in their fields and thus have the ability to seek out original research that is of high scientific impact and quality.</p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Objective: </strong> To advance the osteopathic medical profession through the promotion of the <em>JAOA</em> as the premier scientific research journal for the publication of original contributions.</p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Methods: </strong> Up to 54 <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Board members were tasked with promoting the <em>JAOA</em> to their colleagues as an outlet for publishing original contributions. Because Editorial Board members are cognizant in their ability to influence osteopathic research, the <em>JAOA</em> expected to see an increase in the number of original contribution submissions. </p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong>Results:</strong> <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Board members were especially persuasive in their efforts to spark conversation among their colleagues regarding original contributions to the <em>JAOA</em>, encouraging more structurally efficient and innovative research to be published in the <em>JAOA</em>.</p><p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong>Conclusion: </strong> The quantity and quality of original contributions submitted to the <em>JAOA</em> was at an all-time high, thus advancing the osteopathic medical profession. </p>','<p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(253, 197, 120); line-height: 22px; margin: 10px 20px; text-align: left;\">The American Osteopathic Association (AOA) is pleased to announce its 14th editor in chief, Robert Orenstein, DO. Currently an associate professor of medicine at the Mayo Clinic College of Medicine in Rochester, Minnesota, and the chair of the Division of Infectious Diseases at the Mayo Clinic in Phoenix, Arizona, Dr Orenstein began contributing to <em> The Journal of the American Osteopathic Association </em> <em>(JAOA)</em> in 2010 as a section editor of “Evidence-Based Clinical Reviews.”</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(17, 31, 67); line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin: 3px 20px 6px; text-align: left;\">NEWS RELEASE: <a href= \"http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/news-and-publications/media-center/2014-news-releases/Pages/1-10-american-ostoeopathic-association-names-mayo-clinic-academic-leader-as-its-new-editor-in-chief.aspx\"> American Osteopathic Association Names Mayo Clinic Academic Leader as its New Editor in Chief </a> </p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px 15px; text-align: left;\">Do you have promotional ideas or strategies? Questions or concerns? Did you know that the <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Board’s online workspace allows you to start a discussion with fellow board members?</p>','http://www.osteopathic.org/committees/JAOA-editorial-board/Lists/Team%20Discussion/AllItems.aspx','<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(17, 31, 67); margin-top: 3px;\">Michael M. Patterson, PhD</h2>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">Professor of Osteopathic Medicine, Retired; Associate Editor, <em>JAOA</em>.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">University of Iowa, Class of 1969; University of California, Irvine, Class of 1971.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">as a teacher and researcher in the osteopathic profession since 1971, I feel it is part of my professional responsibility to be active in the profession. For the past 26 years, I have served as a <em>JAOA</em> contributing or associate editor, and I have found this role to be an excellent way to give a bit back to the osteopathic profession.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">how well the authors have conveyed their message to the readership of the <em>JAOA</em>. Is the manuscript clear, concise, and well laid out?</p>','mpatterson.jpg',NULL),(93,'Editorial Board','Winter',2014,'<h1>***HEADLINE***</h1>','<p>***MAIN*BODY*TEXT***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN*KICKER***</p>','<p>***ONLINE*POLL*QUESTION***</p>','http://','<h2>***PEER*NAME***</h2>','<p>***PEER*OCCUPATION***</p>','<p>***PEER*SCHOOL***</p>','<p>***PEER*INVOLVED*BECAUSE***</p>','<p>***PEER*WHEN*REVIEWING***</p>','mpatterson.jpg ',NULL),(94,'Editorial Advisory Board','Winter',2014,'<h1 style=\"color: rgb(17, 31, 76); font-size: 15px; line-height: 20px; margin: 10px 20px;\"><em>JAOA</em> Editorial Advisory Board Member Potential: An Original Contribution Abstract</h1>','<p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"></p><p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Context: </strong> <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Advisory Board members are experts in their fields and thus have the ability to seek out original research that is of high scientific impact and quality.</p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Objective: </strong> To advance the osteopathic medical profession through the promotion of the <em>JAOA</em> as the premier scientific research journal for the publication of original contributions.</p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong> Methods: </strong> Up to 12 <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Advisory Board members were tasked with promoting the <em>JAOA</em> to their colleagues as an outlet for publishing original contributions. Because Editorial Advisory Board members are cognizant in their ability to influence osteopathic research, the <em>JAOA</em> expected to see an increase in the number of original contribution submissions. </p> <p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong>Results:</strong> <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Advisory Board members were especially persuasive in their efforts to spark conversation among their colleagues regarding original contributions to the <em>JAOA</em>, encouraging more structurally efficient and innovative research to be published in the <em>JAOA</em>.</p><p id=\"main_body_text_to_edit\" style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px; text-align: left;\" class=\"main_body_text_to_edit\"> <strong>Conclusion: </strong> The quantity and quality of original contributions submitted to the <em>JAOA</em> was at an all-time high, thus advancing the osteopathic medical profession. </p>','<p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(253, 197, 120); line-height: 22px; margin: 10px 20px; text-align: left;\">The American Osteopathic Association (AOA) is pleased to announce its 14th editor in chief, Robert Orenstein, DO. Currently an associate professor of medicine at the Mayo Clinic College of Medicine in Rochester, Minnesota, and the chair of the Division of Infectious Diseases at the Mayo Clinic in Phoenix, Arizona, Dr Orenstein began contributing to <em> The Journal of the American Osteopathic Association </em> <em>(JAOA)</em> in 2010 as a section editor of “Evidence-Based Clinical Reviews.”</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 14px; color: rgb(17, 31, 67); line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; margin: 3px 20px 6px; text-align: left;\">NEWS RELEASE: <a href=\"http://www.osteopathic.org/inside-aoa/news-and-publications/media-center/2014-news-releases/Pages/1-10-american-ostoeopathic-association-names-mayo-clinic-academic-leader-as-its-new-editor-in-chief.aspx\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 31, 67);\"> American Osteopathic Association Names Mayo Clinic Academic Leader as its New Editor in Chief </a> </p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px 20px 10px 15px; text-align: left;\">Do you have promotional ideas or strategies? Questions or concerns? Did you know that the <em>JAOA</em> Editorial Advisory Board’s online workspace allows you to start a discussion with fellow board members?</p>','http://http://www.osteopathic.org/committees/JAOA-editorial-advisory-board/Lists/Team%20Discussion/AllItems.aspx','<h2 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 17px; color: rgb(17, 31, 67); margin-top: 3px;\">Michael M. Patterson, PhD</h2>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">Professor of Osteopathic Medicine, Retired; Associate Editor, <em>JAOA</em>.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">University of Iowa, Class of 1969; University of California, Irvine, Class of 1971.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">as a teacher and researcher in the osteopathic profession since 1971, I feel it is part of my professional responsibility to be active in the profession. For the past 26 years, I have served as a <em>JAOA</em> contributing or associate editor, and I have found this role to be an excellent way to give a bit back to the osteopathic profession.</p>','<p style=\"font-size: 13px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 17px; margin: 0px; text-align: left;\">how well the authors have conveyed their message to the readership of the <em>JAOA</em>. Is the manuscript clear, concise, and well laid out?</p>','mpatterson.jpg',NULL),(95,'Peer Reviewers','Summer',2014,'<h1>***HEADLINE***</h1>','<p>***MAIN*BODY*TEXT***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN*KICKER***</p>','<p>***ONLINE*POLL*QUESTION***</p>','http://','<h2>***PEER*NAME***</h2>','<p>***PEER*OCCUPATION***</p>','<p>***PEER*SCHOOL***</p>','<p>***PEER*INVOLVED*BECAUSE***</p>','<p>***PEER*WHEN*REVIEWING***</p>','patterson.jpg',NULL),(96,'Peer Reviewers','Summer',2014,'<h1>***HEADLINE***</h1>','<p>***MAIN*BODY*TEXT***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN*KICKER***</p>','<p>***ONLINE*POLL*QUESTION***</p>','http://','<h2>***PEER*NAME***</h2>','<p>***PEER*OCCUPATION***</p>','<p>***PEER*SCHOOL***</p>','<p>***PEER*INVOLVED*BECAUSE***</p>','<p>***PEER*WHEN*REVIEWING***</p>','mpatterson.jpg',NULL),(97,'Peer Reviewers','Summer',2014,'<h1>***HEADLINE***</h1>','<p>***MAIN*BODY*TEXT***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN*KICKER***</p>','<p>***ONLINE*POLL*QUESTION***</p>','http://','<h2>***PEER*NAME***</h2>','<p>***PEER*OCCUPATION***</p>','<p>***PEER*SCHOOL***</p>','<p>***PEER*INVOLVED*BECAUSE***</p>','<p>***PEER*WHEN*REVIEWING***</p>','mpatterson.jpg',NULL),(98,'Peer Reviewers','Summer',2014,'<h1>***HEADLINE***</h1>','<p>***MAIN*BODY*TEXT***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN***</p>','<p>***LEAD*IN*KICKER***</p>','<p>***FEEDBACK*REQUEST*TEXT***</p>','http://','<h2>**